WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.860
I'm going to focus on the mosanitizumab and polatizumab vedotin for relapsed refractory

00:00:05.860 --> 00:00:07.280
diffused B-cell lymphomas.

00:00:07.700 --> 00:00:09.480
These are my financial disclosures.

00:00:10.440 --> 00:00:17.540
So as the audience is aware, mosanitizumab is CD3-CD20 targeting bispecific T-cell engager

00:00:17.540 --> 00:00:22.320
antibody, and it is approved for follicular lymphoma in the third-line settings.

00:00:22.800 --> 00:00:29.040
In addition, polatizumab vedotin is an antibody drug conjugate targeting CD79B, and it's

00:00:29.040 --> 00:00:34.380
approved in the front-line setting for DLBCL and also in the relapsed settings.

00:00:35.100 --> 00:00:41.100
So the combination, which was thought to be synergistic, and also the polatizumab is thought

00:00:41.100 --> 00:00:47.560
to increase the expiration of CD20 and potentiating the effect of mosanitizumab for lymphoma cell

00:00:47.560 --> 00:00:47.840
killing.

00:00:48.440 --> 00:00:51.760
So that was the rationale for doing this phase 2 trial.

00:00:52.140 --> 00:00:56.520
Patients with relapsed large B-cell lymphoma receiving one prior lines of therapies, including

00:00:57.140 --> 00:00:58.940
CD20 targeting treatment.

00:00:59.040 --> 00:01:00.060
They were eligible.

00:01:00.460 --> 00:01:05.140
Patients who were ineligible for stem cell transplant were enrolled in this trial.

00:01:05.700 --> 00:01:11.460
The study design included intravenous mosanitizumab in the step of fashion in the first cycle

00:01:11.700 --> 00:01:15.560
and subsequently every three weeks for a total of 17 cycles.

00:01:16.200 --> 00:01:21.540
Patients who achieve CR at cycle 8 can stop treatment at that moment, but patients who had

00:01:21.540 --> 00:01:26.040
partial remission at cycle 8 can finish a total of 17 cycles.

00:01:26.400 --> 00:01:27.800
Polatizumab was given intravenously at every three weeks.

00:01:27.800 --> 00:01:27.900
Polatizumab was given intravenously at every three weeks.

00:01:27.900 --> 00:01:27.980
Polatizumab was given intravenously at every three weeks.

00:01:27.980 --> 00:01:28.040
Polatizumab was given intravenously at every three weeks.

00:01:28.040 --> 00:01:28.100
Polatizumab was given intravenously at every three weeks.

00:01:28.100 --> 00:01:28.140
Polatizumab was given intravenously at every three weeks.

00:01:28.140 --> 00:01:28.200
Polatizumab was given intravenously at every three weeks.

00:01:28.200 --> 00:01:34.460
at every three weeks interval for a total of six cycles. The trial did not require any mandatory

00:01:34.460 --> 00:01:40.920
hospitalization for CRS management, sorry, for CRS monitoring. So in the phase two portion,

00:01:40.920 --> 00:01:46.640
a total of 98 patients were enrolled. Majority of the patients had deep field large B-cell lymphoma

00:01:46.640 --> 00:01:56.180
and close to 60% of patients had germinal center origin as a cell of origin. Median lines of

00:01:56.180 --> 00:02:02.800
prior therapy were true. One-third of patients received prior CAR-T-cell therapy and half of

00:02:02.800 --> 00:02:08.740
the patients had primary refractory disease. The efficacy results for three years of follow-up

00:02:08.740 --> 00:02:14.700
results were presented at ASH last year and the complete response rates, as you can see,

00:02:14.780 --> 00:02:22.260
is 50% among all 98 patients, but also in patients who had primary refractory disease, CRS were 44%.

00:02:22.260 --> 00:02:25.780
Patients who had prior CAR-T-cell therapy, 50%.

00:02:26.180 --> 00:02:30.740
And refractory to prior CAR-T-cell therapy, the CRS were 42%.

00:02:30.740 --> 00:02:36.620
Now, moving on to the overall response rates, the manuscript was indeed published a few years ago

00:02:36.620 --> 00:02:43.800
in the Nature Medicine Journal, and it also showed that overall response rates and complete response

00:02:43.800 --> 00:02:49.160
rates, they were seen across all subgroups. The three years follow-up results, which were

00:02:49.160 --> 00:02:54.420
presented at ASH, showed that median duration of response was 24 months on the left side of the

00:02:54.420 --> 00:02:55.360
upper plot.

00:02:56.180 --> 00:03:00.880
Among patients who had CAR-T-cell therapy, median duration of response was close to four years,

00:03:01.260 --> 00:03:07.620
showing that this combination can provide durable remissions. The median duration of complete

00:03:07.620 --> 00:03:13.960
response was close to four years among all patient populations, and patients who had CAR-T-cell

00:03:13.960 --> 00:03:18.660
therapy, median duration of complete response rate was close to four years. So pretty much

00:03:18.660 --> 00:03:26.020
patients who respond to this combination, they can derive durable remissions, and there are very few

00:03:26.180 --> 00:03:27.720
late recurrences noted.

00:03:27.720 --> 00:03:34.600
Progression-free survival at three years was approximately 30%, but among those patients who received

00:03:34.600 --> 00:03:40.420
CAR-T-cell therapy, three-year progression-free survival was approximately 40%. Three-year

00:03:40.420 --> 00:03:52.260
overall survival was 42% among all patient population, and the survival was 44% among CAR-T-cell

00:03:52.260 --> 00:03:53.860
therapy recipient patients.

00:03:53.860 --> 00:04:02.100
The CRS rates are very important to analyze here. The rate of cytokine release syndrome was close to 19

00:04:02.100 --> 00:04:10.120
patients, and a majority of CRS were mild, and mild grade 1 and grade 2. Median time to onset of CRS was

00:04:10.120 --> 00:04:17.700
one day after the last dose, and the duration was two doses. As you can see, all CRS were reversible

00:04:17.700 --> 00:04:19.580
with the help of supportive treatment.

00:04:20.720 --> 00:04:22.860
ICANN's rates were 5%.

00:04:22.860 --> 00:04:23.840
The other advantage was that the CRS rate was very low, and the duration was two doses. The CRS rate was

00:04:23.840 --> 00:04:29.000
adverse events of interest were grade 3 for neutropenia, 20%, and grade 3 for serious

00:04:29.000 --> 00:04:34.760
infections, which were 9%. So overall, this combination has manageable safety profile in

00:04:34.760 --> 00:04:40.240
the relapsed large cell lymphoma settings. Now, moving on to the next step, based on this exciting

00:04:40.240 --> 00:04:48.060
phase 2 data, which we participated, the company went on to perform phase 3 trial, which was

00:04:48.060 --> 00:04:54.300
mucinotuzumab-polartuzumab comparing to R-GEMOX, which was a phase 3 Sunmo trial. The results were

00:04:54.300 --> 00:05:00.720
presented at ICML last year and published in JCO last year. So I'll quickly go over with those

00:05:00.720 --> 00:05:06.760
data as well. The study's design was the same as phase 2. Patients with relapsed large cell

00:05:06.760 --> 00:05:12.740
lymphoma receiving one prior line subtherapies were randomized 2 to 1 to outpatient subcutaneous

00:05:12.740 --> 00:05:17.360
mucinotuzumab 8 cycles and 6 cycles of polartuzumab intravenously.

00:05:17.940 --> 00:05:18.040
These were the results of the trial. The results were presented at ICML last year and published in JCO last year.

00:05:18.040 --> 00:05:24.280
The other control group was R-GEMOX, and patients received R-GEMOX in the standard fashion for a

00:05:24.280 --> 00:05:32.020
total of 8 cycles. A total of approximately 200 patients were enrolled in this study,

00:05:32.380 --> 00:05:40.920
138 in the mucin and pola, and 70 patients in R-GEMOX. Median age was 63 years, approximately 63

00:05:40.920 --> 00:05:48.020
years in both age groups. Majority of the patients had B-cell lymphoma. Median lines of prior lines

00:05:48.020 --> 00:05:55.100
of therapies were 2, and approximately 57 to 60 percent of patients had primary refractory disease.

00:05:55.680 --> 00:06:00.540
So the primary endpoint was progression-free survival, and as you can see with the green

00:06:00.540 --> 00:06:05.620
curve, which represents mucin and polartuzumab-vedotin combination, mucin and polan

00:06:05.620 --> 00:06:12.240
significantly improved progression-free survival compared to R-GEMOX with a hazard ratio of 0.41.

00:06:12.240 --> 00:06:18.000
At 18 months, progression-free survival was 39 percent with the combination versus for

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:25.140
14 percent in the R-GEMOX group. The subgroup analysis showed that the combination improved

00:06:25.140 --> 00:06:30.880
PFS in all the important subgroups, including relapse and refractory settings, second line

00:06:30.880 --> 00:06:36.960
versus third line plus settings. Importantly, the combination had higher rate of complete

00:06:36.960 --> 00:06:42.280
remission rates, 51 percent, which is what we observed in the phase 2 settings, but the CRS

00:06:42.280 --> 00:06:47.700
were essentially double than the current R-GEMOX standard of care chemotherapy arm.

00:06:47.980 --> 00:06:56.560
Complete responses were durable at 18 months. Duration of complete response was 65 percent with

00:06:56.560 --> 00:07:03.440
the combination versus 44 percent in the R-GEMOX arm, and the median duration of complete response

00:07:03.440 --> 00:07:08.640
in the mucin and polartuzumab did not reach. The side effects were essentially the same what we

00:07:08.640 --> 00:07:13.420
observed in the phase 2 component, and also the R-GEMOX side effects were also the similar

00:07:13.420 --> 00:07:17.960
in what we expect. So fixed duration, mucin and polartuzumab,

00:07:17.960 --> 00:07:23.740
has demonstrated high and clinically meaningful responses in relapse-refractory large base cell

00:07:23.740 --> 00:07:30.540
lymphoma in both phase 2 and phase 3 SUNMO trial. The safety profile supports this use for outpatient

00:07:30.540 --> 00:07:37.340
care, and mucin and polartuzumab offers a fixed duration outpatient regimen for patients with

00:07:37.340 --> 00:07:43.180
relapse-refractory large base cell lymphoma in transplant-ineligible comorbid or post-carticel

00:07:43.180 --> 00:07:44.800
therapy settings. Thank you so much.
